I submitted an idea to BP <TIMEX3 tid="t21" type="DATE" value="PAST_REF">a few days ago</TIMEX3> which I believe will work , to stop the leak .
They already have a 78 ton metal box which they can put on top of the leak on the ocean floor .
I suggest they start vacuuming mud off the sea bed and dumping the mud on top of the box .
Eventually , the mud will build up a large roughly conical mound on top of , and around , the box and leak .
The weight of the mud bearing down on the box will seal it effectively against the sea bed .
The sheer mass of mud will counteract the overpressure of the oil from the well .
The relief well <TIMEX3 tid="t23" type="DATE" value="PRESENT_REF">currently</TIMEX3> being drilled will eventually remove the oil overpressure , so the mud can then be removed by pumps and the leak sealed in a more permanent fashion .
